Subject: [PATCH] Revert to using default colors from lscolors
Patch-Source: https://github.com/sharkdp/fd/issues/1635

---
By default, fd uses some arbitrarily chosen foreground colours, which
are low contrast and unreadable on light backgrounds.

Remove the hardcoded defaults, and use the terminal's current colour
theme instead. This uses the same colours as programs like `ls`, and is
almost always what the user expects.

Fixes: https://github.com/sharkdp/fd/issues/1635
